  task aud_tests "Audience surface tests" {
    depends !aud_graph_rendering, !aud_animations
    task aud_unit_tests "Component / styling unit tests" {
      effort 2d
      allocate team
    }
    task aud_behavior_tests "BDD scenarios — 'audience sees N1 land, transition agreed, etc.'" {
      effort 2d
      allocate team
    }
    task aud_playwright_e2e "Playwright E2E tests for the audience page" {
      effort 2d
      allocate team
      note "Drive the actual audience URL in a browser, simulating live event arrivals."
    }
    task aud_visual_regression "Visual-regression tests (screenshots) for state styling" {
      effort 2d
      allocate team
      depends !aud_playwright_e2e
      note -8<-
        Layout determinism + first-mount fit + broadcast spacing land in aud_layout_engine
        (commit on 2026-05-27). This task asserts the resulting pixel output matches a
        checked-in fixture for a representative graph — the natural verification layer for
        video-clarity properties the Vitest layer cannot pin. Source: aud_layout_engine Decision §5.

        Typography pixel-stability also deferred here per aud_clean_typography Decision §6
        (component not yet reachable). This task must also assert that font-family/size/weight
        render identically across Chrome/Firefox/WebKit at 720p/1080p/1440p; reference-image
        fixtures cover the codepoint ranges confirmed by packages/i18n-catalogs/src/typography.test.ts.
        Source: tasks/refinements/audience/aud_clean_typography.md.

        Agreed-state styling pixel-stability also deferred here per aud_agreed_styling Decision §5.
        Assert that a node + edge whose rollupStatus is 'agreed' renders at border-color / line-color
        #334155 (slate-700) across Chrome/Firefox/WebKit at 720p/1080p/1440p, against the same
        reference fixtures the layout + typography deferrals already pin.
        Source: tasks/refinements/audience/aud_agreed_styling.md.

        Proposed-state styling pixel-stability also deferred here per aud_proposed_styling Decision §6.
        Assert that a node + edge whose rollupStatus is 'proposed' renders with border-style / line-style
        'dashed' and opacity 0.6 across Chrome/Firefox/WebKit at 720p/1080p/1440p, against the same
        reference fixtures the layout + typography + agreed-state deferrals already pin.
        Source: tasks/refinements/audience/aud_proposed_styling.md.

        Disputed-state styling pixel-stability also deferred here per aud_disputed_styling Decision §5.
        Assert that a node whose rollupStatus is 'disputed' renders with border-color #e11d48 + border-width
        3px and an edge renders with line-color + target-arrow-color #e11d48 across Chrome/Firefox/WebKit
        at 720p/1080p/1440p, against the same reference fixtures the layout + typography + agreed-state +
        proposed-state deferrals already pin. Stylesheet correctness and mount-time computed-style are
        fully pinned at the Vitest layer (cases ee–hh in GraphView.test.tsx); this task covers the
        visible pixel rendering only. Source: tasks/refinements/audience/aud_disputed_styling.md.

        Per-facet pill overlay pixel-stability also deferred here per aud_per_facet_visualization
        Decision §6. Assert that a node with three facet pills (wording=agreed, classification=disputed,
        substance=proposed) renders with the per-status palette + canonical wording → classification →
        substance reading order + above-the-node anchor across Chrome/Firefox/WebKit at 720p/1080p/1440p,
        against the same reference fixtures the layout + typography + state-styling deferrals already pin.
        Overlay mount lifecycle, subscription set, per-element placement, and canonical reading order are
        fully pinned at the Vitest layer (PerFacetPillOverlay.test.tsx cases a–j); this task covers the
        visible pixel rendering only. Source: tasks/refinements/audience/aud_per_facet_visualization.md.

        Meta-disagreement-state styling pixel-stability also deferred here per aud_meta_disagreement_split
        Decision §6. Assert that a node whose rollupStatus is 'meta-disagreement' renders with
        border-style: 'double' + border-color #7c3aed (violet-600, inherited border-width: 1) and an edge
        with the same rollup renders with line-color #7c3aed + target-arrow-color #7c3aed (solid, baseline
        width) across Chrome/Firefox/WebKit at 720p/1080p/1440p, against the same reference fixtures the
        layout + typography + agreed-state + proposed-state + disputed-state deferrals already pin.
        Stylesheet correctness, projection-time rollupStatus resolution, and mount-time computed-style are
        fully pinned at the Vitest layer (GraphView.test.tsx cases oo–rr); this task covers the visible
        pixel rendering only. Source: tasks/refinements/audience/aud_meta_disagreement_split.md.

        Annotation badge pixel-stability also deferred here per aud_annotation_rendering Decision §6.
        Assert that a node with two committed annotations (e.g. a 'note' + a 'reframe') renders with the
        amber-100/amber-900 pill palette + commit-arrival horizontal flex-row + correct anchor below the
        axiom-mark row (ANNOTATION_ROW_OFFSET_Y = 30 px below node bounding box) across
        Chrome/Firefox/WebKit at 720p/1080p/1440p, against the same reference fixtures the layout +
        typography + state-styling + per-facet-pill deferrals already pin. Overlay mount lifecycle,
        subscription set, per-element placement, multi-annotation horizontal stack, empty-list omission,
        and cleanup behavior are fully pinned at the Vitest layer (AnnotationOverlay.test.tsx cases a–j);
        this task covers the visible pixel rendering only.
        Source: tasks/refinements/audience/aud_annotation_rendering.md.
      ->8-
    }
